# Documentation style (Markdown)

- Audience: humans. Prefer clarity and brevity; use technical terms only when they aid precision.
- One emphasis style per span (eg: no stacked bold + backticks).
  - Links: `[path/to/file](path/to/file)` — no backticks on link text.
  - Literals (paths, commands, env vars): backticks when not linked; bold for plain emphasis only.
- No emojis, em-dashes, or other non-ASCII punctuation.